          "date": "2014-11-03 17:07:16.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-5849 lnet: lnet_parse_networks return number of nets",
        "message": "LU-5849 lnet: lnet_parse_networks return number of nets\n\nlnet_dyn_add_ni() requires lnet_parse_networks to return\nthe number of nets (outside of LO) that were parsed in\norder to do proper sanity checks.\n\nlnet_parse_networks() maintained the number of nets parsed\nin a local variable nnets, however it didn't retun it.\n\nThe change makes lnet_parse_networks() return the number\nof nets parsed if successful and < 0 if failure.\n\nSigned-off-by: Amir Shehata <amir.shehata@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Idcd23f8c1609d50cb0cfa0930ffbcea539d77921\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
